</div> 
<p><strong>Hand Ballista</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ballistas" href="/Ballistas" target="">Ballista</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Hand Ballista</strong>&nbsp;does not scale with any stat attributes but requires 30&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and 14&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;to wield.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for ranged combat to break an enemies stance for more effective upcoming attacks targeted towards this recipient of this weapon's attacks.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>An unconventional ballistic device modeled on a weapon used to besiege castles. Only capable of firing greatbolts.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>Perfect for reckless acts such as storming a castle or facing an entire army alone.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Hand Ballista in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Hand Ballista weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>At the top of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Forest Lookout Tower" href="/Forest+Lookout+Tower">Forest Lookout Tower</a>, south west of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bridge of Sacrifice" href="/Bridge+of+Sacrifice">Bridge of Sacrifice</a> on the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weeping Peninsula" href="/Weeping+Peninsula">Weeping Peninsula</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=3013&amp;lat=-208.15&amp;lng=114.54&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=3013&amp;lat=-208.15&amp;lng=114.54&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Hand Ballista Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Kick" href="/Kick" target="">Kick</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>C</strong>an be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Ammunition: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ballista Bolt" href="/Ballista+Bolt" target="">Ballista Bolt</a>&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Like all weapons in the crossbow/ballista family, the <strong>Hand Ballista&nbsp;</strong>has no scaling with any stat.</li> 
 <li>While the Hand Ballista is stated to require 30 Strength to use,&nbsp;the actual requirement is only 20 Strength, as the weapon can only be fired two-handed.</li> 
 <li>You cannot shoot bolts while mounted. Instead you will physically hit with the weapon (comes with light and charged attacks).</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Hand Ballista</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the <strong>Hand Ballista</strong> Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Hand Ballista Upgrades in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (1)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(1)" target="">Smithing Stone [1]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (2)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(2)" target="">Smithing Stone [2]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (3)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(3)" target="">Smithing Stone [3]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (4)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(4)" target="">Smithing Stone [4]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (5)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(5)" target="">Smithing Stone [5]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (6)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(6)" target="">Smithing Stone [6]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (7)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(7)" target="">Smithing Stone [7]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (8)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(8)" target="">Smithing Stone [8]</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone" href="/Ancient+Dragon+Smithing+Stone">Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone</a>.</p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
